 <h2>Echo Cavern: Soloing Needlites</h2><br><br><br>Set up in the left corner of needlite room, and pull out a FIRE PET (important!). Buff the pet, but don't give it a DS, it has its own, and its better. In fact its essential for this.<br><br>You can solo these (singles) with your level20 spells, even though they will start out red then! All are single pulls except in the far corner you sometimes get 2.<br><br>Simply pull with a low level nuke, and set your pet on them, healing if needed. These mobs hit weak but fast, making them ideal to be eaten by your pets damage shield!<br><br><br>The only problems with this camp are: The spore plant guarding the ramp - but this is avoidable, just stay away from it and by the walls. It ignores your pet, but sometimes will KS needlites from you if your pet chases them towards it.<br><br>The second problem is the Queen, which is a rare spawn in the center, before 24 you are best off getting someone else to kill it, say its up and usually people will be only too glad to help!<br><br><br><br></center><b><u>Zone Information:</u></b><br><br><a href='http://www.eqmages.com' onClick='moblist(150); return false;'>Echo Caverns mob list</a><br>
<a href='http://www.eqmages.com' onClick='questlist(150); return false;'>Echo Caverns quest list</a><br><a href='http://www.eqatlas.com/luclin/echocaverns.html'>Echo Caverns Map</a><br><br><b><u>Comments/Feedback:</u></b><br><br><i><b>justanothermage</b> says:</i><br>actually i managed to kill the queen when i was lvl 25 shes a bit tough to get rid of usually easiest if you can get buffs for you and your pets... also if you have the torch focus item makesa BIG difference in pets attack and hp<br><br><i><b>Numnah Wishtah</b> says:</i><br>I managed to defeat the Queen at lvl 24. Thankfully I had already cleared the room of all other needlites, so it was just us two to do battle. And my dear fire pet as well ... I tried with the Earth pet, that also works, because needlites run away (towards that horrid ceiling worm thingy), but not as well as my Fire Fluffy worked.
<br><br><i><b>Naladini</b> says:</i><br>Actually, the spore guarding the entrance to the room ignores the needlites (and other mobs) completely. There was a zone issue where sometimes a fleeing mob would "poof" whle trying to leave the room (very close to the spore). 

This may have been fixed with the new collision system patches.

I would also recommend that you get your torch of alna before attempting these encounters. The unfocused firepets don't have many hit points, especially at level 20.<br><br><i><b>Axxil</b> says:</i><br>killed the queen 2 for 2 at lev. 20 now, just make sure your pet has full health and you got plenty oh'mana ;)....

first time she killed my pet and didn't touch me (went into run mode right as he died), and the second time i overnuked, pet lived and i almost bit the big one...

one resist one either battle would have done me in tho, good luck!<br><br><i><b>Meddorick Summons</b> says:</i><br>I camped this area at 24 and managed to kill the Queen 2 times. I was able to handle 2 Needlites at a time with a buffed fire pet and the torch focus item. Took about an hour to level to 25.<br><br><i><b>Rattalious Fenris</b> says:</i><br>Okay i didnt see this any place on this page or the one over at the mob page. These Needlites are one 21 min spawn times, so you might not like this camp since it takes me about 6 or 7 min to clear the room then i have 14 min of waiting with full mana. Not much fun. Just a warning for the impatent.<br><br><i><b>Anonymous</b> says:</i><br>Something to consider when xpin using needlites is the rediculously long spawn time.  I dont know how long it is, but i do waste a lot of buff time sitting instead of fighting.  Other than that, its a great zone. <br><br><i><b>Orley</b> says:</i><br>I bought my pet some toys (11% haste mask and the belt that gives +500hp) Gave him an earthen blade and I was soloing this room at 16.  lol<br><br><i><b>Anonymous</b> says:</i><br>what torch focus item

